## File Length Limit

TypeScript and TSX files must not exceed 500 lines. This is enforced by
`make file_len_check` (part of `make ci`) and in the Biome lint GitHub Actions
workflow.

This limit exists to prevent AI-generated code from becoming monolithic and
forces refactoring into smaller, more modular components.

If a file genuinely needs to exceed 500 lines, add it to the `exclude` list in
`package.json` under `"fileLength"`. Entries must be **repo-relative paths**:

```json
{
    "fileLength": {
        "max_lines": 500,
        "exclude": [
            "onboard.ts",
            "src/main/some-large-module.ts"
        ]
    }
}
```

Do not add files to the exclude list without a clear justification.
